<div id="review_286939686" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/286939686" />
    <a title="Gina&#39;s Library" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1339260-gina-s-library"><img alt="Gina&#39;s Library" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1389676472p2/1339260.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/286939686?book_show_action=true">Mar 01, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Gina&#39;s Library" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Gina&#39;s Library" href="/user/show/1339260-gina-s-library">Gina&#39;s Library</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition 9781941212066" href="/book/show/13229281-widow-virgin-whore">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1339260-gina-s-library?shelf=2012">2012</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer286939686" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5284419296204075159">I read this book for World Literary Cafe. <br/><br/>When you see the book title it makes you do a double take and wonder what in the world you are getting into. Don&apos;t let the title scare you.<br/><br/>I loved this book. I read it in 2 days. <br/><br/>The topic of AIDS to some still in this day and age is a taboo subject. We all know about AIDS but no one really wants to talk about it. <br/><br/>This book is beautifully written. It really makes you stop and see what exactly a person with AIDS goes through. Not just the illness, but the</span>
  <span id="freeText5284419296204075159" style="display:none">I read this book for World Literary Cafe. <br /><br />When you see the book title it makes you do a double take and wonder what in the world you are getting into. Don't let the title scare you.<br /><br />I loved this book. I read it in 2 days. <br /><br />The topic of AIDS to some still in this day and age is a taboo subject. We all know about AIDS but no one really wants to talk about it. <br /><br />This book is beautifully written. It really makes you stop and see what exactly a person with AIDS goes through. Not just the illness, but the emotional toll it takes on you as well. <br /><br />It also shows the different emotions that your friends and family go through as you become weaker. <br /><br />I loved this book. I did tear up a few times. </span>
  <a data-text-id="5284419296204075159" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


